5000|$|The U.S. Navy {{utilized}} an 1802-based {{system in}} the development of their ARCADES (Automatic <b>RADIAC</b> Calibration And Diagnostic Equipment System) Radiation Detection, Indication, and Computation (<b>RADIAC)</b> program at the Oak Ridge National Laboratory (ORNL) in collaboration with Martin Marietta in the 1980s, creating an interface between a reader-logger unit and a computer system, with the hardware implemented as an RCA CDP18S600 single-board computer and the software written in RCA BASIC III interpreter.|$|E
